            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your<strong> chicken stock mix</strong> with 75ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> <span class=\"text-purple\">[100ml]</span> [150ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Cook for 30 secs or until slightly thickened, then reduce the heat to very low and add the<strong> soured cream </strong>and any resting juices from the steaks</p><p>Stir it all together and cook for 1-2 min or until warmed through (don't let it boil!) – this is your<strong> paprikash sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
